HEADWORD: Weldons process
<hw>Wel"don's proc"ess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
process for the recovery or regeneration of manganese dioxide in the
manufacture of chlorine, by means of milk of lime and the oxygen of the
air; -- so called after the inventor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

